/**
 * Project Sentinel - Suppression Technical Blocks
 * Purpose: Renders room readiness checklist, agent comparison matrix, discharge sequence timelines, and pre-quote summaries.
 * Dependencies: Astro section layout, SVG.
 * Structural Role: Presentation component for suppression page.
 */
<section class="section-padding bg-white">
  <div class="mx-auto max-w-7xl px-6">

    <!-- Block 1: Protected Room Readiness Checklist -->
    <div>
      <span class="text-sm font-bold uppercase tracking-wider text-kharon-purple">Room Readiness</span>
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold leading-tight text-kharon-black mt-2">Protected room readiness checklist</h2>
      <p class="mt-5 text-lg leading-8 text-kharon-grey max-w-3xl">
        Before a gas suppression system can be commissioned, the protected enclosure must meet strict integrity standards. Every item below must be verified.
      </p>

      <div class="mt-10 grid gap-5 sm:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3">
        <div class="rounded-lg border border-kharon-border p-5 bg-white flex items-start gap-4">
          <svg class="mt-0.5 h-5 w-5 shrink-0 text-kharon-purple" viewBox="0 0 20 20" fill="currentColor" aria-hidden="true">
            <path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M16.707 5.293a1 1 0 010 1.414l-8 8a1 1 0 01-1.414 0l-4-4a1 1 0 011.414-1.414L8 12.586l7.293-7.293a1 1 0 011.414 0z" clip-rule="evenodd"/>
          </svg>
          <div>
            <p class="font-semibold text-kharon-black">Sealed cable/pipe penetrations</p>
            <p class="mt-1 text-sm text-kharon-grey">All cable trays, conduits and pipework sealed with rated fire-stopping to maintain room integrity.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="rounded-lg border border-kharon-border p-5 bg-white flex items-start gap-4">
          <svg class="mt-0.5 h-5 w-5 shrink-0 text-kharon-purple" viewBox="0 0 20 20" fill="currentColor" aria-hidden="true">
            <path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M16.707 5.293a1 1 0 010 1.414l-8 8a1 1 0 01-1.414 0l-4-4a1 1 0 011.414-1.414L8 12.586l7.293-7.293a1 1 0 011.414 0z" clip-rule="evenodd"/>
          </svg>
          <div>
            <p class="font-semibold text-kharon-black">Automatic door closers fitted</p>
            <p class="mt-1 text-sm text-kharon-grey">Every access door must be self-closing to prevent agent loss during discharge.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="rounded-lg border border-kharon-border p-5 bg-white flex items-start gap-4">
          <svg class="mt-0.5 h-5 w-5 shrink-0 text-kharon-purple" viewBox="0 0 20 20" fill="currentColor" aria-hidden="true">
            <path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M16.707 5.293a1 1 0 010 1.414l-8 8a1 1 0 01-1.414 0l-4-4a1 1 0 011.414-1.414L8 12.586l7.293-7.293a1 1 0 011.414 0z" clip-rule="evenodd"/>
          </svg>
          <div>
            <p class="font-semibold text-kharon-black">Drop seals on all doors</p>
            <p class="mt-1 text-sm text-kharon-grey">Threshold gaps sealed with automatic drop-down seals to stop agent escaping under doors.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="rounded-lg border border-kharon-border p-5 bg-white flex items-start gap-4">
          <svg class="mt-0.5 h-5 w-5 shrink-0 text-kharon-purple" viewBox="0 0 20 20" fill="currentColor" aria-hidden="true">
            <path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M16.707 5.293a1 1 0 010 1.414l-8 8a1 1 0 01-1.414 0l-4-4a1 1 0 011.414-1.414L8 12.586l7.293-7.293a1 1 0 011.414 0z" clip-rule="evenodd"/>
          </svg>
          <div>
            <p class="font-semibold text-kharon-black">Warning signage at all entry points</p>
            <p class="mt-1 text-sm text-kharon-grey">Bilingual warning signs installed at every entrance indicating gas suppression hazard.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="rounded-lg border border-kharon-border p-5 bg-white flex items-start gap-4">
          <svg class="mt-0.5 h-5 w-5 shrink-0 text-kharon-purple" viewBox="0 0 20 20" fill="currentColor" aria-hidden="true">
            <path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M16.707 5.293a1 1 0 010 1.414l-8 8a1 1 0 01-1.414 0l-4-4a1 1 0 011.414-1.414L8 12.586l7.293-7.293a1 1 0 011.414 0z" clip-rule="evenodd"/>
          </svg>
          <div>
            <p class="font-semibold text-kharon-black">Abort switches accessible</p>
            <p class="mt-1 text-sm text-kharon-grey">Manual abort stations positioned at each exit for emergency cancellation of discharge.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="rounded-lg border border-kharon-border p-5 bg-white flex items-start gap-4">
          <svg class="mt-0.5 h-5 w-5 shrink-0 text-kharon-purple" viewBox="0 0 20 20" fill="currentColor" aria-hidden="true">
            <path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M16.707 5.293a1 1 0 010 1.414l-8 8a1 1 0 01-1.414 0l-4-4a1 1 0 011.414-1.414L8 12.586l7.293-7.293a1 1 0 011.414 0z" clip-rule="evenodd"/>
          </svg>
          <div>
            <p class="font-semibold text-kharon-black">Dedicated ventilation dampers</p>
            <p class="mt-1 text-sm text-kharon-grey">HVAC dampers must close on activation and reopen for post-discharge purge.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Block 2: Agent Selection Matrix -->
    <div class="mt-16">
      <span class="text-sm font-bold uppercase tracking-wider text-kharon-purple">Agent Comparison</span>
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold leading-tight text-kharon-black mt-2">Agent selection matrix</h2>
      <p class="mt-5 text-lg leading-8 text-kharon-grey max-w-3xl">
        Each suppression agent carries different environmental, spatial, safety and cost profiles. Kharon selects the right agent based on the protected risk, not stock preference.
      </p>

      <div class="mt-10 grid gap-5 md:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-4">
        <!-- FM-200 -->
        <article class="rounded-lg border border-kharon-border p-6 bg-white">
          <p class="text-xs font-bold uppercase text-kharon-purple">Chemical Clean Agent</p>
          <h3 class="mt-3 text-xl font-bold text-kharon-black">FM-200</h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-kharon-grey">HFC-227ea</p>
          <dl class="mt-5 space-y-3">
            <div class="flex justify-between text-sm">
              <dt class="text-kharon-grey">ODP</dt>
              <dd class="font-semibold text-kharon-black">0</dd>
            </div>
            <div class="flex justify-between text-sm">
              <dt class="text-kharon-grey">GWP</dt>
              <dd class="font-semibold text-kharon-black">High</dd>
            </div>
            <div class="flex justify-between text-sm">
              <dt class="text-kharon-grey">Space Required</dt>
              <dd class="font-semibold text-kharon-black">Low</dd>
            </div>
            <div class="flex justify-between text-sm">
              <dt class="text-kharon-grey">Personnel Safety</dt>
              <dd class="font-semibold text-kharon-black">Safe at design conc.</dd>
            </div>
            <div class="flex justify-between text-sm">
              <dt class="text-kharon-grey">Cost Tier</dt>
              <dd class="font-semibold text-kharon-black">$$</dd>
            </div>
          </dl>
          <p class="mt-5 text-sm leading-6 text-kharon-grey border-t border-kharon-border pt-4">
            <span class="font-semibold text-kharon-black">Typical use:</span> IT rooms, telecommunications spaces, small server enclosures.
          </p>
        </article>

        <!-- Inergen -->
        <article class="rounded-lg border border-kharon-border p-6 bg-white">
          <p class="text-xs font-bold uppercase text-kharon-purple">Inert Gas Blend</p>
          <h3 class="mt-3 text-xl font-bold text-kharon-black">Inergen</h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-kharon-grey">IG-541</p>
          <dl class="mt-5 space-y-3">
            <div class="flex justify-between text-sm">
              <dt class="text-kharon-grey">ODP</dt>
              <dd class="font-semibold text-kharon-black">0</dd>
            </div>
            <div class="flex justify-between text-sm">
              <dt class="text-kharon-grey">GWP</dt>
              <dd class="font-semibold text-kharon-black">0</dd>
            </div>
            <div class="flex justify-between text-sm">
              <dt class="text-kharon-grey">Space Required</dt>
              <dd class="font-semibold text-kharon-black">High</dd>
            </div>
            <div class="flex justify-between text-sm">
              <dt class="text-kharon-grey">Personnel Safety</dt>
              <dd class="font-semibold text-kharon-black">Safe (inert)</dd>
            </div>
            <div class="flex justify-between text-sm">
              <dt class="text-kharon-grey">Cost Tier</dt>
              <dd class="font-semibold text-kharon-black">$$$</dd>
            </div>
          </dl>
          <p class="mt-5 text-sm leading-6 text-kharon-grey border-t border-kharon-border pt-4">
            <span class="font-semibold text-kharon-black">Typical use:</span> Archives, heritage buildings, museums, long-term storage.
          </p>
        </article>

        <!-- Novec 1230 -->
        <article class="rounded-lg border border-kharon-border p-6 bg-white">
          <p class="text-xs font-bold uppercase text-kharon-purple">Fluoroketone</p>
          <h3 class="mt-3 text-xl font-bold text-kharon-black">Novec 1230</h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-kharon-grey">FK-5-1-12</p>
          <dl class="mt-5 space-y-3">
            <div class="flex justify-between text-sm">
              <dt class="text-kharon-grey">ODP</dt>
              <dd class="font-semibold text-kharon-black">0</dd>
            </div>
            <div class="flex justify-between text-sm">
              <dt class="text-kharon-grey">GWP</dt>
              <dd class="font-semibold text-kharon-black">1</dd>
            </div>
            <div class="flex justify-between text-sm">
              <dt class="text-kharon-grey">Space Required</dt>
              <dd class="font-semibold text-kharon-black">Low</dd>
            </div>
            <div class="flex justify-between text-sm">
              <dt class="text-kharon-grey">Personnel Safety</dt>
              <dd class="font-semibold text-kharon-black">Safe</dd>
            </div>
            <div class="flex justify-between text-sm">
              <dt class="text-kharon-grey">Cost Tier</dt>
              <dd class="font-semibold text-kharon-black">$$$</dd>
            </div>
          </dl>
          <p class="mt-5 text-sm leading-6 text-kharon-grey border-t border-kharon-border pt-4">
            <span class="font-semibold text-kharon-black">Typical use:</span> Data centres, clean rooms, high-value electronic environments.
          </p>
        </article>

        <!-- CO2 -->
        <article class="rounded-lg border border-kharon-red/30 p-6 bg-red-50">
          <p class="text-xs font-bold uppercase text-kharon-red">High Pressure Gas</p>
          <h3 class="mt-3 text-xl font-bold text-kharon-black">CO<span class="text-base">2</span></h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-kharon-grey">Carbon Dioxide</p>
          <dl class="mt-5 space-y-3">
            <div class="flex justify-between text-sm">
              <dt class="text-kharon-grey">ODP</dt>
              <dd class="font-semibold text-kharon-black">0</dd>
            </div>
            <div class="flex justify-between text-sm">
              <dt class="text-kharon-grey">GWP</dt>
              <dd class="font-semibold text-kharon-black">0</dd>
            </div>
            <div class="flex justify-between text-sm">
              <dt class="text-kharon-grey">Space Required</dt>
              <dd class="font-semibold text-kharon-black">Moderate</dd>
            </div>
            <div class="flex justify-between text-sm">
              <dt class="text-kharon-grey">Personnel Safety</dt>
              <dd class="font-bold text-kharon-red">LETHAL</dd>
            </div>
            <div class="flex justify-between text-sm">
              <dt class="text-kharon-grey">Cost Tier</dt>
              <dd class="font-semibold text-kharon-black">$</dd>
            </div>
          </dl>
          <p class="mt-5 text-sm leading-6 text-kharon-grey border-t border-kharon-red/20 pt-4">
            <span class="font-semibold text-kharon-black">Typical use:</span> Unmanned plant rooms, machinery spaces, areas with no personnel risk.
          </p>
        </article>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Block 3: Discharge Sequence Diagram -->
    <div class="mt-16">
      <span class="text-sm font-bold uppercase tracking-wider text-kharon-purple">System Sequence</span>
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold leading-tight text-kharon-black mt-2">Discharge sequence diagram</h2>
      <p class="mt-5 text-lg leading-8 text-kharon-grey max-w-3xl">
        From first detection to post-discharge ventilation, every stage is timed, audibly signalled and logged for compliance traceability.
      </p>

      <div class="mt-10 w-full max-w-4xl mx-auto overflow-x-auto">
        <svg class="w-full min-w-[44rem]" viewBox="0 0 900 160" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" role="img" aria-label="Discharge sequence timeline" font-family="system-ui, -apple-system, sans-serif">
          <defs>
            <marker id="arrow-cyan" markerWidth="8" markerHeight="8" refX="7" refY="4" orient="auto" markerUnits="strokeWidth">
              <path d="M0,0 L8,4 L0,8 z" fill="#00C2FF"/>
            </marker>
          </defs>

          <!-- Connecting lines -->
          <line x1="75" y1="80" x2="165" y2="80" stroke="#00C2FF" stroke-width="2" marker-end="url(#arrow-cyan)"/>
          <line x1="225" y1="80" x2="315" y2="80" stroke="#00C2FF" stroke-width="2" marker-end="url(#arrow-cyan)"/>
          <line x1="375" y1="80" x2="465" y2="80" stroke="#00C2FF" stroke-width="2" marker-end="url(#arrow-cyan)"/>
          <line x1="525" y1="80" x2="615" y2="80" stroke="#00C2FF" stroke-width="2" marker-end="url(#arrow-cyan)"/>
          <line x1="675" y1="80" x2="765" y2="80" stroke="#00C2FF" stroke-width="2" marker-end="url(#arrow-cyan)"/>

          <!-- Node 1: Detection Trigger -->
          <circle cx="50" cy="80" r="22" fill="#4B2E83"/>
          <text x="50" y="84" text-anchor="middle" fill="#FFFFFF" font-size="11" font-weight="bold">01</text>
          <text x="50" y="125" text-anchor="middle" fill="#0B0D0F" font-size="11" font-weight="600">Detection</text>
          <text x="50" y="142" text-anchor="middle" fill="#2B3138" font-size="10">Trigger</text>

          <!-- Node 2: Stage 1 Pre-alarm -->
          <circle cx="200" cy="80" r="22" fill="#4B2E83"/>
          <text x="200" y="84" text-anchor="middle" fill="#FFFFFF" font-size="11" font-weight="bold">02</text>
          <text x="200" y="125" text-anchor="middle" fill="#0B0D0F" font-size="11" font-weight="600">Stage 1</text>
          <text x="200" y="142" text-anchor="middle" fill="#2B3138" font-size="10">Pre-alarm</text>

          <!-- Node 3: Countdown Timer -->
          <circle cx="350" cy="80" r="22" fill="#4B2E83"/>
          <text x="350" y="84" text-anchor="middle" fill="#FFFFFF" font-size="11" font-weight="bold">03</text>
          <text x="350" y="125" text-anchor="middle" fill="#0B0D0F" font-size="11" font-weight="600">Countdown</text>
          <text x="350" y="142" text-anchor="middle" fill="#2B3138" font-size="10">30-60s</text>

          <!-- Node 4: Agent Release -->
          <circle cx="500" cy="80" r="22" fill="#4B2E83"/>
          <text x="500" y="84" text-anchor="middle" fill="#FFFFFF" font-size="11" font-weight="bold">04</text>
          <text x="500" y="125" text-anchor="middle" fill="#0B0D0F" font-size="11" font-weight="600">Agent</text>
          <text x="500" y="142" text-anchor="middle" fill="#2B3138" font-size="10">Release</text>

          <!-- Node 5: Hold Period -->
          <circle cx="650" cy="80" r="22" fill="#4B2E83"/>
          <text x="650" y="84" text-anchor="middle" fill="#FFFFFF" font-size="11" font-weight="bold">05</text>
          <text x="650" y="125" text-anchor="middle" fill="#0B0D0F" font-size="11" font-weight="600">Hold</text>
          <text x="650" y="142" text-anchor="middle" fill="#2B3138" font-size="10">Period</text>

          <!-- Node 6: Post-discharge Ventilation -->
          <circle cx="800" cy="80" r="22" fill="#4B2E83"/>
          <text x="800" y="84" text-anchor="middle" fill="#FFFFFF" font-size="11" font-weight="bold">06</text>
          <text x="800" y="125" text-anchor="middle" fill="#0B0D0F" font-size="11" font-weight="600">Post-discharge</text>
          <text x="800" y="142" text-anchor="middle" fill="#2B3138" font-size="10">Ventilation</text>

          <!-- Top labels -->
          <text x="200" y="35" text-anchor="middle" fill="#00C2FF" font-size="10" font-weight="600">Visual / Audible</text>
          <text x="350" y="35" text-anchor="middle" fill="#00C2FF" font-size="10" font-weight="600">Abort window</text>
          <text x="500" y="35" text-anchor="middle" fill="#00C2FF" font-size="10" font-weight="600">Damper close</text>
          <text x="650" y="35" text-anchor="middle" fill="#00C2FF" font-size="10" font-weight="600">Concentration hold</text>
        </svg>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Block 4: Pre-Quote Data Capture Summary -->
    <div class="mt-16">
      <span class="text-sm font-bold uppercase tracking-wider text-kharon-purple">Pre-Quote Requirements</span>
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold leading-tight text-kharon-black mt-2">Pre-quote data capture summary</h2>
      <p class="mt-5 text-lg leading-8 text-kharon-grey max-w-3xl">
        Accurate quoting requires precise room data. Providing these details upfront avoids site revisits and ensures the design is sized correctly from day one.
      </p>

      <div class="mt-10 grid gap-5 md:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3">
        <div class="rounded-lg border border-kharon-border p-6 bg-white">
          <p class="font-semibold text-kharon-black">Protected room dimensions</p>
          <p class="mt-2 text-sm leading-6 text-kharon-grey">Length, width and clear height to the underside of the slab. Used to calculate agent volume and cylinder count.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="rounded-lg border border-kharon-border p-6 bg-white">
          <p class="font-semibold text-kharon-black">Number of doors and openable windows</p>
          <p class="mt-2 text-sm leading-6 text-kharon-grey">Every opening affects retention time calculations and determines sealing, damper and abort-switch requirements.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="rounded-lg border border-kharon-border p-6 bg-white">
          <p class="font-semibold text-kharon-black">Cable / pipe penetration count</p>
          <p class="mt-2 text-sm leading-6 text-kharon-grey">Unsealed penetrations are the most common cause of integrity test failure. A count informs fire-stopping scope.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="rounded-lg border border-kharon-border p-6 bg-white">
          <p class="font-semibold text-kharon-black">Floor construction</p>
          <p class="mt-2 text-sm leading-6 text-kharon-grey">Raised access, solid slab or void beneath the room. Determines pipe routing, nozzle placement and sub-floor detection.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="rounded-lg border border-kharon-border p-6 bg-white">
          <p class="font-semibold text-kharon-black">Existing detection system</p>
          <p class="mt-2 text-sm leading-6 text-kharon-grey">Is detection already present? What type (smoke, heat, aspiration)? Compatibility with suppression release panels varies.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="rounded-lg border border-kharon-border p-6 bg-white">
          <p class="font-semibold text-kharon-black">24/7 occupancy status</p>
          <p class="mt-2 text-sm leading-6 text-kharon-grey">Continuously occupied rooms require safer agents, longer countdown timers and additional abort logic.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

  </div>
</section>
